In Arnoldus-Lewis v Murphy [2008] NSWSC 1103;  BC200809350 , McCallum J treated an order for the payment of expenses made by a Local Court Magistrate sitting in the Small Claims Division as an error going to lack of jurisdiction within the meaning of LCA 1982 s 73(2) (now LCA 2007 
s 39(2)
) rather then “mere error in the exercise of jurisdiction” (in which case no appeal would have been possible), the lack of jurisdiction point not being taken by the unrepresented respondent to the appeal. An appeal to the Court of Appeal was unsuccessful:  Murphy v Arnoldus-Lewis [2009] NSWCA 142;  BC200904994 .
